User Story
I want the report cover page to reflect the latest UI design,
So that it is aligned with design.
* To fetch the data of Workmanship from SSO
** The workmanship is beyond / within AQL
**** number of CRI / number of MAJ / number of MIN
**** When the found > allowed, then display (!)
**** number allowed for CRI / number allowed for MAJ / number allowed for MIN
** If the workmanship in N/A or no data,
*** do not map to either NON-CONFORMITIES or ALSO WORTH NOTING
* When BEYOND, then display this part
* When WITHIN, then display this part

Given that I am a report reader, that I can find the workmanship beyond / within / N/A cases in different parts of  report cover page with expected data according to the conditions. column1: After check code logic in PSI make report available, I found there has two “Make Report available to Client“ button in PSI order page.
Another is in “Report Cover & Bonus“ page

There is a setting in customer to control where to display. And if click “Make Report available to Client“ button in “*Report Cover & Bonus*“ page, REPORT_TO_CLIENT_ON in the ORDER_PROD_REPORT table will be null. Because in this case, PSI does not save the time into REPORT_TO_CLIENT_ON field.

And I wrote a SQL to check how many finished orders REPORT_TO_CLIENT_ON is null. The data in this Excel is for report submit time in 2024. Over 5,000 reports, I don't know if this is a bug or a feature. 😆
ogi.ORDER_ID, ogi.ORDER_NUMBER, ogi.SERVICE_TYPE, op.PRODUCT_ID, ogi.ACTUAL_INSP_DATE, ogi.ORDER_PLACER, cc.COMPANY_NAME, opr.REPORT_SUBMIT_TIME
left join ORDER_PRODUCT op on op.ORDER_ID = ogi.ORDER_ID
left join ORDER_PROD_REPORT opr on opr.PRODUCT_ID = op.PRODUCT_ID
left join CRM_COMPANY cc on cc.ID = ogi.COMPANY_ID
I just found another table also has “REPORT_TO_CLIENT_ON“ field.

And if the customer settings “Make report available to client“ is “Per order“, click “make report available“ button will update date in this table. Otherwise both tables will be updated at the same time.","24/Jul/24 4:40 PM;619dbe81b0b630006abd8fc7;h2. QA Note:
fix: the column REPORT_TO_CLIENT_ON in the ORDER_PROD_REPORT table null
h3. Section Testing Suggestion(s) for QA to test:
# Set the customer settings “Make report available to client“ is “Per order“.
# Use this cusetomer create an order and finish it.
# Click ”Make Reports available to Client” button in “Report Cover & Bonus“ page.
# Use sql to check if column is null.
{noformat}select PRODUCT_ID, REPORT_TO_CLIENT_ON from ORDER_PROD_REPORT where PRODUCT_ID = 'xxx';{noformat}

column3: Before Make report available to client, it’s empty in the table for the data
column6: After Make report available to client, it’s not empty in the table for the data

Given that I am a client, when I book DURPO type that I can be able to see the new field with 2 options.

column1: * Currently the “factory management” button at order level in IRP is only accessible for manager role “IRP: Coordination manager“, while in daily operations it’s usually the specialist / supervisor that needs to create data, who instead just edit the plain text at order level, which causes more data issues and repetitive work.
* To add the new role “IRP: Coordination team” for this button
** So that coordination specialist, supervisor, leader and manager can all access and manage factory master data.

column1: [ReFlow] Improve the email template and validate the cancel payment API,SP-18167,138036,Improvement,Done,SP,Services Platform,software,Simon Zhong,557058:27505318-8f08-426d-8d08-0b74d4507cba,,,High,Waiting to Release,louis.yi,61650ecdd9820f0070140c5c,Jen Zheng,712020:d2e16699-bbaa-4b17-908f-fb17ea363453,Jen Zheng,712020:d2e16699-bbaa-4b17-908f-fb17ea363453,22/Jul/24 2:36 PM,26/Jul/24 4:11 PM,26/Jul/24 5:22 PM,26/Jul/24 4:10 PM,SP-202407-W31,,0,,"[https://qima.atlassian.net/browse/SP-16895

## Cancel the limitation for waiting 5min to pay → back end effort
# Support ReFlow updated their calculation logic
